ARGOCD is Kubernetes Native deployment tool it gives good user interface and we can easily automate yml deployment process

Example this is my cluster which have one control plane and 2 worker nodes 

Suppose any developer who write yaml file and connect to cluster and apply directly 

Above example developer directly connected to cluster to run yaml files ------ WIthout ArgoCD

Same example lets see with ARGO CD - we need to push the yaml files to source code repo github repo so you need to integarte ARGO CD - SO it always watches if any yaml files comes it will sync with cluster always 

so in above example once we integrated with argocd insider cluster argocd githubrepo
so if any developer pushed changes automatically apply those changes to cluster and this process is called gitops process.

developer push code --> docker file --> image push ---> ecr --> yaml push to github(apply ) (UNTIL THIS PROCESS IS CALLED CI)-->argocd integration (THIS PROCESS is called CD -) --> Kubernetes  control plane --> worker nodes

